Fig. 3. Example frame from the MPPI-based local planner operating
in a cluttered environment. The planner generates a smooth trajectory
(cyan dashed line) toward the goal (green marker) while avoiding obstacles
represented by the costmap heatmap. The green arrow denotes the desired
velocity from MPPI, the red arrow shows the robot’s actual velocity, and
the black arrow indicates the current heading. The planner commands an
angular velocity of 0.29 rad/s, while the measured yaw rate is 0.06 rad/s

